 Earth Sciences, University College London, London, WC1E 6BT, UK</p><p class="c-article-author-affiliation__authors-list">Andrew R. Thomson</p></li></ol><div class="u-js-hide u-hide-print" data-test="author-info"><span class="c-article__sub-heading">Authors</span><ol class="c-article-authors-search u-list-reset"><li id="auth-Andrew_R_-Thomson-Aff1-Aff2"><span class="c-article-authors-search__title u-h3 js-search-name">Andrew R. Thomson</span><div class="c-article-authors-search__list"><div class="c-article-authors-search__item c-article-authors-search__list-item--left"><a href="/search?author=Andrew%20R.%20Thomson" class="c-article-button" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - publication" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">View author publications</a></div><div class="c-article-authors-search__item c-article-authors-search__list-item--right"><p class="search-in-title-js c-article-authors-search__text"><span class="c-article-authors-search__links-text">Search author on:</span><span class="c-article-identifiers"><a class="c-article-identifiers__item" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=search&amp;term=Andrew%20R.%20Thomson" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - pubmed" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">PubMed</a><span class="u-hide"> </span><a class="c-article-identifiers__item" href="https://scholar.google.co.uk/scholar?as_q=&amp;num=10&amp;btnG=Search+Scholar&amp;as_epq=&amp;as_oq=&amp;as_eq=&amp;as_occt=any&amp;as_sauthors=%22Andrew%20R.%20Thomson%22&amp;as_publication=&amp;as_ylo=&amp;as_yhi=&amp;as_allsubj=all&amp;hl=en" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - scholar" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">Google Scholar</a></span></p></div></div></li><li id="auth-Michael_J_-Walter-Aff1"><span class="c-article-authors-search__title u-h3 js-search-name">Michael J. Walter</span><div class="c-article-authors-search__list"><div class="c-article-authors-search__item c-article-authors-search__list-item--left"><a href="/search?author=Michael%20J.%20Walter" class="c-article-button" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - publication" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">View author publications</a></div><div class="c-article-authors-search__item c-article-authors-search__list-item--right"><p class="search-in-title-js c-article-authors-search__text"><span class="c-article-authors-search__links-text">Search author on:</span><span class="c-article-identifiers"><a class="c-article-identifiers__item" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=search&amp;term=Michael%20J.%20Walter" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - pubmed" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">PubMed</a><span class="u-hide"> </span><a class="c-article-identifiers__item" href="https://scholar.google.co.uk/scholar?as_q=&amp;num=10&amp;btnG=Search+Scholar&amp;as_epq=&amp;as_oq=&amp;as_eq=&amp;as_occt=any&amp;as_sauthors=%22Michael%20J.%20Walter%22&amp;as_publication=&amp;as_ylo=&amp;as_yhi=&amp;as_allsubj=all&amp;hl=en" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - scholar" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">Google Scholar</a></span></p></div></div></li><li id="auth-Simon_C_-Kohn-Aff1"><span class="c-article-authors-search__title u-h3 js-search-name">Simon C. Kohn</span><div class="c-article-authors-search__list"><div class="c-article-authors-search__item c-article-authors-search__list-item--left"><a href="/search?author=Simon%20C.%20Kohn" class="c-article-button" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - publication" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">View author publications</a></div><div class="c-article-authors-search__item c-article-authors-search__list-item--right"><p class="search-in-title-js c-article-authors-search__text"><span class="c-article-authors-search__links-text">Search author on:</span><span class="c-article-identifiers"><a class="c-article-identifiers__item" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=search&amp;term=Simon%20C.%20Kohn" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - pubmed" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">PubMed</a><span class="u-hide"> </span><a class="c-article-identifiers__item" href="https://scholar.google.co.uk/scholar?as_q=&amp;num=10&amp;btnG=Search+Scholar&amp;as_epq=&amp;as_oq=&amp;as_eq=&amp;as_occt=any&amp;as_sauthors=%22Simon%20C.%20Kohn%22&amp;as_publication=&amp;as_ylo=&amp;as_yhi=&amp;as_allsubj=all&amp;hl=en" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - scholar" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">Google Scholar</a></span></p></div></div></li><li id="auth-Richard_A_-Brooker-Aff1"><span class="c-article-authors-search__title u-h3 js-search-name">Richard A. Brooker</span><div class="c-article-authors-search__list"><div class="c-article-authors-search__item c-article-authors-search__list-item--left"><a href="/search?author=Richard%20A.%20Brooker" class="c-article-button" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - publication" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">View author publications</a></div><div class="c-article-authors-search__item c-article-authors-search__list-item--right"><p class="search-in-title-js c-article-authors-search__text"><span class="c-article-authors-search__links-text">Search author on:</span><span class="c-article-identifiers"><a class="c-article-identifiers__item" href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=search&amp;term=Richard%20A.%20Brooker" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - pubmed" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">PubMed</a><span class="u-hide"> </span><a class="c-article-identifiers__item" href="https://scholar.google.co.uk/scholar?as_q=&amp;num=10&amp;btnG=Search+Scholar&amp;as_epq=&amp;as_oq=&amp;as_eq=&amp;as_occt=any&amp;as_sauthors=%22Richard%20A.%20Brooker%22&amp;as_publication=&amp;as_ylo=&amp;as_yhi=&amp;as_allsubj=all&amp;hl=en" data-track="click" data-track-action="author link - scholar" data-track-label="link" rel="nofollow">Google Scholar</a></span></p></div></div></li></ol></div><h3 class="c-article__sub-heading" id="contributions">Contributions</h3><p>A.R.T. designed, performed and analysed the experiments, gathered data from the literature and wrote the manuscript as part of his PhD studies. M.J.W. and S.C.K. provided training in experimental techniques, assisted during interpretation of results, provided advice and assisted with manuscript preparation in their roles as A.R.T.’s PhD supervisors. R.A.B. provided training and assistance with experimental techniques and sample preparation alongside contributing to the scientific content and preparation of the manuscript.</p><h3 class="c-article__sub-heading" id="corresponding-author">Corresponding author</h3><p id="corresponding-author-list">Correspondence to
                <a id="corresp-c1" aria-label="email Andrew R. Thomson" href="mailto:a.r.thomson@ucl.ac.uk">Andrew R. Thomson</a>.</p></div></div></section><section data-title="Ethics declarations"><div class="c-article-section" id="ethics-section"><h2 class="c-article-section__title js-section-title js-c-reading-companion-sections-item" id="ethics">Ethics declarations</h2><div class="c-article-section__content" id="ethics-content">
              
                <h3 class="c-article__sub-heading">Competing interests</h3>
                <p>The authors declare no competing financial interests.</p>
              
            </div></div></section><section data-title="Extended data figures and tables"><div class="c-article-section" id="Sec11-section"><h2 class="c-article-section__title js-section-title js-c-reading-companion-sections-item" id="Sec11">Extended data figures and tables</h2><div class="c-article-section__content" id="Sec11-content"><div data-test="supplementary-info"><div id="figshareContainer" class="c-article-figshare-container" data-test="figshare-container"></div><div class="c-article-supplementary__item js-c-reading-companion-figures-item" data-test="supp-item" id="Fig5"><h3 class="c-article-supplementary__title u-h3"><a class="print-link" data-track="click" data-track-action="view supplementary info" data-test="supp-info-link" data-track-label="extended data figure 1 comparison of experimental " href="/articles/nature16174/figures/5" data-supp-info-image="//media.springernature.com/lw685/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1038%2Fnature16174/MediaObjects/41586_2016_Article_BFnature16174_Fig5_ESM.jpg">Extended Data Figure 1 Comparison of experimental compositions with natural rocks.</a></h3><div class="c-article-supplementary__description" data-component="thumbnail-container"><p><b>a</b>–<b>f</b>, ‘Fresh’ MORB rocks (red field), ALL-MORB<sup><a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 21" title="Gale, A., Dalton, C. A., Langmuir, C. H., Su, Y. &amp; Schilling, J.-G. The mean composition of ocean ridge basalts. Geochem. Geophys. Geosyst. 14, 489–518 (2013)" href="/articles/nature16174#ref-CR21" id="ref-link-section-d18338277e1731">21</a></sup> (red circle), altered MORB rocks<sup><a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 41" title="Kelley, K. A., Plank, T., Ludden, J. &amp; Staudigel, H. Composition of altered oceanic crust at ODP Sites 801 and 1149. Geochem. Geophys. Geosyst. 4, 6 (2003)" href="/articles/nature16174#ref-CR41" id="ref-link-section-d18338277e1735">41</a></sup> (pale blue circles), exhumed blueschist, greenschist and/or eclogitic rocks (yellow circles) and starting material from this (dark blue circle) and previous studies (green circles) of carbonated MORB compositions. In <b>a</b>, rocks altered MORB and exhumed rock compositions that fall on the Mg-Fe side of the maj–cpx join from <a data-track="click" data-track-label="link" data-track-action="figure anchor" href="/articles/nature16174#Fig9">Extended Data Fig. 5</a> plot below the dashed line, compositions that lie on the Ca side of this join are plotted as orange circles with yellow outlines or purple circles with blue outlines and sit above the dashed curve. This confirms that magnesite will be the stable carbonate phase at high pressure in the vast majority of natural crustal rocks, as is the case for ATCM1. Data and corresponding references for this figure are provided in the online source data file.</p><p>
                          <a data-track="click" data-track-label="link" data-track-action="supplementary material anchor" href="/articles/nature16174#MOESM274">Source data</a>
                        </p></div></div><div class="c-article-supplementary__item js-c-reading-companion-figures-item" data-test="supp-item" id="Fig6"><h3 class="c-article-supplementary__title u-h3"><a class="print-link" data-track="click" data-track-action="view supplementary info" data-test="supp-info-link" data-track-label="extended data figure 2 experimental results/phase " href="/articles/nature16174/figures/6" data-supp-info-image="//media.springernature.com/lw685/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1038%2Fnature16174/MediaObjects/41586_2016_Article_BFnature16174_Fig6_ESM.jpg">Extended Data Figure 2 Experimental results/phase diagram and interpreted solidus position.</a></h3><div class="c-article-supplementary__description" data-component="thumbnail-container"><p>The reactions clinopyroxene + CO<sub>2 </sub>= dolomite + 2coesite and dolomite = magnesite + aragonite are from refs <a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 22" title="Martin, A. M., Laporte, D., Koga, K. T., Kawamoto, T. &amp; Hammouda, T. Experimental study of the stability of a dolomite + coesite assemblage in contact with peridotite: implications for sediment-mantle interaction and diamond formation during subduction. J. Petrol. 53, 391–417 (2012)" href="/articles/nature16174#ref-CR22" id="ref-link-section-d18338277e1773">22</a> and <a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 23" title="Luth, R. W. Experimental determination of the reaction aragonite + magnesite = dolomite at 5 to 9 GPa. Contrib. Mineral. Petrol. 141, 222–232 (2001)" href="/articles/nature16174#ref-CR23" id="ref-link-section-d18338277e1776">23</a> respectively. The upper left curve is the anhydrous MORB solidus. Note that due to temperature gradients in experiments at 8 GPa, a small quantity of dolomite is observed coexisting with melt in one experiment above the solidus, present at the cold end of the capsule. arag, aragonite; CM, carbonatite melt; cpx, clinopyroxene; cs, coesite; dol, dolomite; gt, garnet; mag, magnesite; maj, majoritic garnet; Na carb, Na carbonate; ox, FeTi oxide; SM, silicate melt; st, stishovite.</p></div></div><div class="c-article-supplementary__item js-c-reading-companion-figures-item" data-test="supp-item" id="Fig7"><h3 class="c-article-supplementary__title u-h3"><a class="print-link" data-track="click" data-track-action="view supplementary info" data-test="supp-info-link" data-track-label="extended data figure 3 bse images of experimental " href="/articles/nature16174/figures/7" data-supp-info-image="//media.springernature.com/lw685/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1038%2Fnature16174/MediaObjects/41586_2016_Article_BFnature16174_Fig7_ESM.jpg">Extended Data Figure 3 BSE images of experimental products.</a></h3><div class="c-article-supplementary__description" data-component="thumbnail-container"><p><b>a</b>, 7.9 GPa, 1,250 °C; <b>b</b>, 7.9 GPa, 1,350 °C; <b>c</b>, 13.1 GPa, 1,350 °C; <b>d</b>, 13.1 GPa; 1,450 °C; <b>e</b>, 20.7 GPa, 1,100 °C; <b>f</b>, 20.7 GPa, 1,480 °C; <b>g</b>, 20.7 GPa, 1,600 °C; <b>h</b>, sandwich experiment, 20.7 GPa, 1,400 °C. Scale bars, 10 μm. CM, carbonatite melt; cpx, clinopyroxene; dol, dolomite; FeTi, FeTi oxide; gt, garnet; mag, magnesite.</p></div></div><div class="c-article-supplementary__item js-c-reading-companion-figures-item" data-test="supp-item" id="Fig8"><h3 class="c-article-supplementary__title u-h3"><a class="print-link" data-track="click" data-track-action="view supplementary info" data-test="supp-info-link" data-track-label="extended data figure 4 composition of experimental" href="/articles/nature16174/figures/8" data-supp-info-image="//media.springernature.com/lw685/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1038%2Fnature16174/MediaObjects/41586_2016_Article_BFnature16174_Fig8_ESM.jpg">Extended Data Figure 4 Composition of experimental melts from this study.</a></h3><div class="c-article-supplementary__description" data-component="thumbnail-container"><p><b>a</b>, <b>b</b>, Experimental melts from selected previous studies marked with semi-transparent greyscale symbols. <b>b</b>, The effects of increasing pressure, temperature and the effect of contamination due to partial analysis of silicate minerals surrounding small melt pools are shown.</p></div></div><div class="c-article-supplementary__item js-c-reading-companion-figures-item" data-test="supp-item" id="Fig9"><h3 class="c-article-supplementary__title u-h3"><a class="print-link" data-track="click" data-track-action="view supplementary info" data-test="supp-info-link" data-track-label="extended data figure 5 the composition of experime" href="/articles/nature16174/figures/9" data-supp-info-image="//media.springernature.com/lw685/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1038%2Fnature16174/MediaObjects/41586_2016_Article_BFnature16174_Fig9_ESM.jpg">Extended Data Figure 5 The composition of experimental phases from this study projected into two quaternary plots.</a></h3><div class="c-article-supplementary__description" data-component="thumbnail-container"><p><b>a</b>, <b>b</b>, [Ca]-[Mg+Fe<sup>2+</sup>]-[Si+Ti]-[Na+K] (<b>a</b>) and [Mg+Fe<sup>2+</sup>]-[Ca]-[Al+Fe<sup>3+</sup>]-[Na+K] (<b>b</b>). In both diagrams the grey fields are the compositional data projected onto the basal ternary. The red field is the range of natural MORB compositions projected onto the basal ternary. The yellow star plotted in the four-component system and projected onto the basal ternary is ATCM1 (our bulk composition) while the black stars are bulk compositions from previous studies<sup><a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 25" title="Litasov, K., Shatskiy, A., Ohtani, E. &amp; Yaxley, G. Solidus of alkaline carbonatite in the deep mantle. Geology 41, 79–82 (2013)" href="/articles/nature16174#ref-CR25" id="ref-link-section-d18338277e1893">25</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 26" title="Syracuse, E. M., van Keken, P. E. &amp; Abers, G. A. The global range of subduction zone thermal models. Phys. Earth Planet. Inter. 183, 73–90 (2010)" href="/articles/nature16174#ref-CR26" id="ref-link-section-d18338277e1896">26</a>,<a data-track="click" data-track-action="reference anchor" data-track-label="link" data-test="citation-ref" aria-label="Reference 27" title="Hammouda, T. &amp; Laporte, D. Ultrafast mantle impregnation by carbonatite melts. Geology 28, 283–285 (2000)" href="/articles/nature16174#ref-CR27" id="ref-link-section-d18338277e1899">27</a></sup>.</p></div></div><div class="c-article-supplementary__item js-c-reading-companion-figures-item" data-test="supp-item" id="Fig10"><h3 class="c-article-supplementary__title u-h3"><a class="print-link" data-track="click" data-track-action="view supplementary info" data-test="supp-info-link" data-track-label="extended data figure 6 bse images of reaction expe" href="/articles/nature16174/figures/10" data-supp-info-image="//media.springernature.com/lw685/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1038%2Fnature16174/MediaObjects/41586_2016_Article_BFnature16174_Fig10_ESM.jpg">Extended Data Figure 6 BSE images of reaction experiments.</a></h3><div class="c-article-supplementary__description" data-component="thumbnail-container"><p><b>a</b>–<b>d</b>, G169 (<b>a</b>, <b>b</b>) and G177 (<b>c</b>, <b>d</b>). In both experiments a reaction zone and remaining carbonatite melt surrounds the unreacted peridotite region. <b>a</b>, An overview of G169. <b>b</b>, A close up of the reaction in G169 containing newly crystallized calcium perovskite, majorite, ferropericlase and ringwoodite minerals. <b>c</b>, A close up of the reaction products in G177, which consist of small bright calcium perovskites, new majorite that is often observed as a rim on relic peridotitic garnet and ringwoodite. <b>d</b>, An overview of G177. CaPv, calcium perovskite; fper, ferropericlase; maj, majorite; rw, ringwoodite; wad, wadsleyite.</p><p>
                          <a data-track="click" data-track-label="link" data-track-action="supplementary material anchor" href="/articles/nature16174#MOESM275">Source data</a>
                        </p></div></div><div class="c-article-supplementary__item js-c-reading-companion-figures-item" data-test="supp-item" id="Fig11"><h3 class="c-article-supplementary__title u-h3"><a class="print-link" data-track="click" data-track-action="view supplementary info" data-test="supp-info-link" data-track-label="extended data figure 7 raman spectra of minerals f" href="/articles/nature16174/figures/11" data-supp-info-image="//media.springernature.com/lw685/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1038%2Fnature16174/MediaObjects/41586_2016_Article_BFnature16174_Fig11_ESM.jpg">Extended Data Figure 7 Raman spectra of minerals from reaction experiment G177 measured using a blue 455 cm<sup>−1</sup> excitation laser.</a></h3><div class="c-article-supplementary__description" data-component="thumbnail-container"><p>The position of the main peaks in each collected spectrum have been labelled with their shift from the excitation laser in cm<sup>−1</sup>.</p></div></div><div class="c-article-supplementary__item js-c-reading-companion-figures-item" data-test="supp-item" id="Fig12"><h3 class="c-article-supplementary__title u-h3"><a class="print-link" data-track="click" data-track-action="view supplementary info" data-test="supp-info-link" data-track-label="extended data figure 8 comparison of diamond-hoste" href="/articles/nature16174/figures/12" data-supp-info-image="//media.springernature.com/lw685/springer-static/image/art%3A10.1038%2Fnature16174/MediaObjects/41586_2016_Article_BFnature16174_Fig12_ESM.jpg">Extended Data Figure 8 Comparison of diamond-hosted calcium perovskite inclusions with experimental mineral compositions in MgO versus Ti number space.</a></h3><div class="c-article-supplementary__description" data-component="thumbnail-container"><p>Ti number = Ti/[Ca+Ti]. Data and corresponding references for this figure are provided in the online source data file.</p></div></div><div class="c-article-supplementary__item" data-test="supp-item"><div class="c-article-table" data-test="inline-table" data-container-section="table" id="table-1"><figure><figcaption class="c-article-table__figcaption"><b id="Tab1" data-test="table-caption">Extended Data Table 1 Starting materials used in this and previous studies</b></figcaption><div class="u-text-right u-hide-print"><a class="c-article__pill-button" data-test="table-link" data-track="click" data-track-action="view table" data-track-label="button" rel="nofollow" href="/articles/nature16174/tables/1" aria-label="Full size table 1"><span>Full size table</span><svg width="16" height="16" focusable="false" role="img" aria-hidden="true" class="u-icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#icon-eds-i-chevron-right-small"></use></svg></a></div></figure></div></div><div class="c-article-supplementary__item" data-test="supp-item"><div class="c-article-table" data-test="inline-table" data-container-section="table" id="table-2"><figure><figcaption class="c-article-table__figcaption"><b id="Tab2" data-test="table-caption">Extended Data Table 2 Summary of run conditions and products for carbonated MORB melting experiments</b></figcaption><div class="u-text-right u-hide-print"><a class="c-article__pill-button" data-test="table-link" data-track="click" data-track-action="view table" data-track-label="button" rel="nofollow" href="/articles/nature16174/tables/2" aria-label="Full size table 2"><span>Full size table</span><svg width="16" height="16" focusable="false" role="img" aria-hidden="true" class="u-icon"><use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#icon-eds-i-chevron-right-small"></use></svg></a></div></figure></div></div><div class="c-article-supplementary__item" data-test="supp-item"><div class="c-article-table" data-test="inline-table" data-container-section="table" id="table-3"><figure><figcaption class="c-article-table__figcaption"><b id="Tab3" data-test="table-caption">Extended Data Table 3 Summary of reaction experiments run conditions and experimenta